			<h2><em>Overview</em></h2><br>
			<div class="row" style="padding-bottom: 2%">
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6 col-md-9">
					<p class="text-justify">Artificial intelligent computer algorithms have gained considerable popularity in many societies. However, some cases suggest algorithms can be biased.</p>
					<p class="text-justify"><strong>How might we encourage ethical algorithm uses?</strong></p>
					<p class="text-justify">After a survey participated by an inclusive group, I discovered an imbalance of power between the algorithm users (data analytics etc.) and the algorithm 'influencees'. Therefore, this project aims to empower algorithm influencees by raising public awareness of the increasing algorithm uses in daily lives, leading to a more socially sustainable society. This is an individual project conducted by myself.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6 col-md-9">
					<div class="accordion" id="accordion01">
						<!-- #1 collapse -->
  						<div class="card">
   							 <div class="card-header" id="headingOne">
      							<h2 class="mb-0">
       								 <button class="btn btn-link" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
      								    What does "algorithm" mean here? 
       								 </button>
     							 </h2>
   							 </div>

  							  <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-parent="#accordion01">
     							 <div class="card-body">
       								 The word "algorithm" in the current project specifically refers to <em>"Artificial Intellengent Computer Algorithms"</em>. For clarity and efficiency, the phrase here is shortened as "algorithm". Many editorial media use the same reference.
     							 </div>
   							 </div>
 						 </div>
						<!-- #2 collapse -->
						<div class="card">
   							 <div class="card-header" id="headingTwo">
      							<h2 class="mb-0">
       								 <button class="btn btn-link" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
      								    Who are <strong>"algorithm influencees"</strong>?
       								 </button>
     							 </h2>
   							 </div>

  							  <div id="collapseTwo" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-parent="#accordion01">
     							 <div class="card-body">
       								 <p>There are various of AI algorithms, many of which can be seen around us, such as facial recognition, product recommendation etc. "Algorithm influencees" refers to whose lives have been affected by the AI algorithms.</p>
									 <p>The word <em>"influencer"</em> can be commonly seen on social media, which refers to a specific group of people whose lifestyles are adored and followed as a trend. By naming the word <em>"influencee"</em>, I was trying to emphasis on the power relationship between AI algorithm users and target data sources("the public").</p>
     							 </div>
   							 </div>
 						 </div>
						<!-- #3 collapse -->
						<div class="card">
