			<h2><em>Ethnographic Research: How well do people know about algorithms?</em></h2><br>
			<div class="row" style="padding-bottom: 2%">
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6 col-md-9">
					<p class="text-justify">My online questionnaire and interviews received 41 quality respondents from 4 ethnic groups ranging from 20 to 70 years old. I discovered that most participants had limited understandings of how AI algorithms might affect their lives. Based on attitude towards algorithm applications and willingness to act, I categorized participants as three different personas shown in the image below. <br><br>Inspired by the results, the current project should focus on raising public awareness, equipping people with knowledge, and encouraging individual responses. The project should act as a preparation for a further transition towards more ethical algorithm uses and robust systems.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6 col-md-9">
					<img src="../resources/images/cLAA_01.JPG" width="100%">
				</div>
			</div>
			<br><br>
			
			<h2><em>Deliverable: A Poster Campaign Concept</em></h2><br>
			<div class="row" style="padding-bottom: 2%">
				<div class="col-12 col-lg-6 col-md-9">
					<p class="text-justify">The deliverable of the project consists of 4 different posters plus a website. The four posters describing four different AI algorithm applications shall be placed in their relevant scenario. For example, the navigation can be seen on buses or undergrounds. Each poster shows a simple task usually done by a computer program, putting the audience in the position of an AI algorithm.</p>
				</div>
